   note = {- also transit-amplifying cell (yellow in fig)<br/>- continuous formation of axillary meristems that ultimately give rise to new branches, prevents the uniform distribution of somatic mutations throughout the shoot<br/>- In dicots, SAM structure is layered, meaning that the displacement of  stem  cells  and  their  fate  is  partially  restricted  by  prevalence of  anticlinal  cell  divisions:  such structure enhances the retention of mutated cell clones, for example, in the form of stable periclinal chimeras},
